# Force LF in every working tree, including Windows checkouts. Several tests assert BYTE-IDENTICAL fixtures
# (dashboard baselines, source-scan regexes over \n, goal-loop prompt parity); a windows-latest runner sets
# core.autocrlf=true machine-wide, which would rewrite the checkout to CRLF and fail them all. Node, bash,
# PowerShell 5.1+, and git handle LF files fine on Windows, so LF everywhere is the honest single truth.
* text=auto eol=lf
# real binaries — never normalized
*.png binary
*.icns binary
*.ico binary
*.bin binary
